SIMPLE: discourser
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discourser
<hw>Dis*cours"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who discourse; a narrator; a speaker; an haranguer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In his conversation he was the most clear
<qex>discourser</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The writer of a treatise or dissertation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Philologers and critical <qex>discoursers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discoursive</ent>⟦br⟧
